PN,30709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782857895
OL,3,CStarmer hails 'game-changing'
OL,4,Cinvestment as delayed defence plan to
OL,5,Cbe unveiled
OL,7,FBritain has been closely watching the
OL,8,Fuse of drones in the theatre of war in
OL,9,FUkraine, where some 200,000 are now
OL,10,Fused each month to defend against
OL,11,FRussian forces, and in Iran, where
OL,12,Faround 700 drones were launched each
OL,13,Fday at the height of its war with the
OL,14,FUS and Israel.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782857895
OL,3,CStarmer hails 'game-changing'
OL,4,Cinvestment as delayed defence plan to
OL,5,Cbe unveiled
OL,7,FIn a signal of the pivot towards drone
OL,8,Fwarfare, the MoD has already announced
OL,9,Fthat a fleet of new destroyer warships
OL,10,Fwill no longer appear in the Dip, and
OL,11,Fwill instead be replaced by "hybrid"
OL,12,Fvessels, which will act as command
OL,13,Fhubs for drones.
OL,15,FThe Dip has become widely regarded as
OL,16,Fa legacy issue for Sir Keir, something
OL,17,Fhe can achieve before he stands down
OL,18,Fas Prime Minister and makes way for
OL,19,Fhis likely successor, Andy Burnham.
OL,26,@sD@]OUsD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782857895
OL,3,CStarmer hails 'game-changing'
OL,4,Cinvestment as delayed defence plan to
OL,5,Cbe unveiled
OL,7,FMr Burnham's camp has left open the
OL,8,Fpossibility that it could revisit the
OL,9,FDip, should he either win a contest or
OL,10,Fbe anointed as Labour leader and the
OL,11,Fnext prime minister.
OL,13,FOn Monday, in a speech laying out his
OL,14,Feconomic prospectus for governing the
OL,15,Fcountry, the leadership challenger
OL,16,Fsuggested he wanted to see British-
OL,17,Fbased defence companies favoured in
OL,18,Ffuture military contracts.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782857895
OL,3,CStarmer hails 'game-changing'
OL,4,Cinvestment as delayed defence plan to
OL,5,Cbe unveiled
OL,7,FSpeaking in Manchester, he said: "From
OL,8,Fhere on, every pound raised from
OL,9,Ftaxpayers will work harder for them,
OL,10,Fand that approach will apply fully to
OL,11,Fthe defence investment plan.
OL,13,F"We will make sure that all eligible
OL,14,Fpublic contracts are subject to proper
OL,15,Fsocial value weighting and we will do
OL,16,Fthat to make sure British-based
OL,17,Fcompanies are in a better position to
OL,18,Fwin those contracts."
OL,26,@oD@bOUuD@AOUzD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782857895
OL,3,CStarmer hails 'game-changing'
OL,4,Cinvestment as delayed defence plan to
OL,5,Cbe unveiled
OL,7,FShadow defence secretary James
OL,8,FCartlidge said the plan was "too
OL,9,Flittle, too late", adding: "Too little
OL,10,Fbecause it is barely more money than
OL,11,FJohn Healey and Al Carns resigned over
OL,12,Fwhen they said Britain would be 'less
OL,13,Fsafe'. And too late because the plan
OL,14,Fis now almost a year overdue and only
OL,15,Fbeing rushed through because Keir
OL,16,FStarmer is desperate for a legacy.
OL,26,@pD@]OUqD@QO]qD@\OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782857895
OL,3,CStarmer hails 'game-changing'
OL,4,Cinvestment as delayed defence plan to
OL,5,Cbe unveiled
OL,7,F"This plan is not worth the paper it's
OL,8,Fwritten on ` Keir Starmer is Prime
OL,9,FMinister in name only. The next prime
OL,10,Fminister needs to cut welfare and give
OL,11,Four armed forces the funding they need
OL,12,Fto keep Britain safe. The problem is,
OL,13,Fit doesn't matter who is in charge,
OL,14,Fall Labour MPs want is more benefits.
OL,15,FLabour are now the welfare party."
OL,17,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey,
OL,18,Fmeanwhile, said the plan was "late and
OL,19,Funderfunded", something he described
OL,20,Fas "unforgivable".
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@bO]zD@^OU{D@LO]|D@DOU|D@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782857895
OL,3,CStarmer hails 'game-changing'
OL,4,Cinvestment as delayed defence plan to
OL,5,Cbe unveiled
OL,7,FHe added: "It is a political choice
OL,8,Fthat makes us all less safe, puts jobs
OL,9,Fat risk and threatens businesses
OL,10,Facross the country in supply chains.
OL,11,FThe Government have dangerously short-
OL,12,Fchanged our armed forces when they
OL,13,Fneed urgent investment after years of
OL,14,FConservative negligence. Defence
OL,15,Fchiefs have been forced to make hard
OL,16,Fchoices when they should be given what
OL,17,Fthey need."
OL,26,@oD@KOUyD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30716
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782857895
OL,3,CStarmer hails 'game-changing'
OL,4,Cinvestment as delayed defence plan to
OL,5,Cbe unveiled
OL,7,FDonald Trump expects the UK and other
OL,8,FNato allies to stick to their defence
OL,9,Fspending pledges, the White House said
OL,10,Fon Monday.
OL,12,FAt a crucial Nato summit in Ankara,
OL,13,FTurkey next week, members of the
OL,14,Fdefence alliance are expected to set
OL,15,Fout a "credible path" to spending 5%
OL,16,Fof economic output on defence by 2035
OL,17,F` 3.5% on core defence spending and a
OL,18,Ffurther 1.5% for wider resilience
OL,19,Fspending.
OL,26,@wD@GOUwD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/16
